#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Veḷudvāravagga "
msgstr "1. At Bamboo Gate "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn55.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Tatiyagiñjakāvasathasutta "
msgstr "10. At the Brick Hall (3rd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn55.10:1.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Ānanda said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.10:1.2"
msgid "“kakkaṭo nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako kālaṅkato; "
msgstr "“Sir, the layman named Kakkaṭa has passed away in Nādika. "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.3"
msgid "tassa kā gati, ko abhisamparāyo? "
msgstr "Where has he been reborn in his next life? "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.4"
msgid "Kaḷibho nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako … pe … "
msgstr "The laymen named Kaḷibha, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.5"
msgid "nikato nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako … "
msgstr "Nikata, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.6"
msgid "kaṭissaho nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako … "
msgstr "Kaṭissaha, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.7"
msgid "tuṭṭho nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako … "
msgstr "Tuṭṭha, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.8"
msgid "santuṭṭho nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako … "
msgstr "Santuṭṭha, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.9"
msgid "bhaddo nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako … "
msgstr "Bhadda, and "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.10"
msgid "subhaddo nāma, bhante, ñātike upāsako kālaṅkato; "
msgstr "Subhadda have passed away in Nādika. "

msgctxt "sn55.10:1.11"
msgid "tassa kā gati ko abhisamparāyo”ti? "
msgstr "Where have they been reborn in the next life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.359, sc2
msgctxt "sn55.10:2.1"
msgid "“Kakkaṭo, ānanda, upāsako kālaṅkato pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, the laymen Kakkaṭa, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:2.2"
msgid "Kaḷibho, ānanda … pe … "
msgstr "Kaḷibha, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:2.3"
msgid "nikato, ānanda … "
msgstr "Nikata, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:2.4"
msgid "kaṭissaho, ānanda … "
msgstr "Kaṭissaha, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:2.5"
msgid "tuṭṭho, ānanda … "
msgstr "Tuṭṭha, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:2.6"
msgid "santuṭṭho, ānanda … "
msgstr "Santuṭṭha, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:2.7"
msgid "bhaddo, ānanda … pe … "
msgstr "Bhadda, "

msgctxt "sn55.10:2.8"
msgid "subhaddo, ānanda, upāsako kālaṅkato pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā. "
msgstr "and Subhadda passed away having ended the five lower fetters. They’ve been reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.10:2.9"
msgid "(Sabbe ekagatikā kātabbā.) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn55.10:3.1"
msgid "Paropaññāsa, ānanda, ñātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā. "
msgstr "Over fifty laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended the five lower fetters. They’ve been reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.10:3.2"
msgid "Sādhikanavuti, ānanda, ñātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmino; sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissanti. "
msgstr "More than ninety laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended three fetters, and weakened greed, hate, and delusion. They’re once-returners, who will come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.10:3.3"
msgid "Chātirekāni kho, ānanda, pañcasatāni ñātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā. "
msgstr "In excess of five hundred laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended three fetters. They’re stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn55.10:4.1"
msgid "Anacchariyaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, yaṃ manussabhūto kālaṃ kareyya; "
msgstr "It’s hardly surprising that a human being should pass away. "

msgctxt "sn55.10:4.2"
msgid "tasmiṃ tasmiñce maṃ kālaṅkate upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipucchissatha. Vihesā pesā, ānanda, assa tathāgatassa. "
msgstr "But if you should come and ask me about it each and every time someone passes away, that would be a bother for me. "

msgctxt "sn55.10:4.3"
msgid "Tasmātihānanda, dhammādāsaṃ nāma dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi; yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "So Ānanda, I will teach you the explanation of the Dhamma called ‘the mirror of the teaching’. A noble disciple who has this may declare of themselves: "

msgctxt "sn55.10:4.4"
msgid "‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’. "
msgstr "‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn55.10:5.1"
msgid "Katamo ca so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo; yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "And what is that mirror of the teaching? "

msgctxt "sn55.10:5.2"
msgid "‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.360, sc6
msgctxt "sn55.10:6.1"
msgid "Idhānanda, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.10:6.2"
msgid "Dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.10:6.3"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.10:6.4"
msgid "ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "sn55.10:6.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo; "
msgstr "This is that mirror of the teaching. "

msgctxt "sn55.10:6.6"
msgid "yena samannāgato ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "A noble disciple who has this may declare of themselves: "

msgctxt "sn55.10:6.7"
msgid "‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’”ti. "
msgstr "‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound for awakening.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.10:6.8"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.10:6.9"
msgid "Veḷudvāravaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn55.10:7.1"
msgid "Rājā ogadhadīghāvu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.10:7.2"
msgid "sāriputtāpare duve; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.10:7.3"
msgid "Thapatī veḷudvāreyyā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn55.10:7.4"
msgid "giñjakāvasathe tayoti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
